			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	SocialStay is a mobile start up focused on the hospitality industry. We&rsquo;re looking for an energetic, driven, experienced Project Manager / Producer to join our fun, fast paced team.</p>
<p>
	THE JOB: The Project Manager / Producer is responsible for managing multiple digital projects&nbsp;while collaborating and communicating internally and with clients. You must be very organized,&nbsp;think well on your feet, can track many projects/ initiatives without dropping a detail. Ideal&nbsp;candidate has solid digital experience (project management) and client facing experience. Must&nbsp;be extremely personable and able to work under pressure and fit with a high performance, fun&nbsp;and committed team. Must be savvy and love web and mobile tools and be comfortable taking&nbsp;initiative and have strong organization skills.</p>
<p>
	RESPONSIBILITIES:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Pro-actively manage projects by implementing the structure, schedule, budgets and</li>
	<li>
		keeping them on track</li>
	<li>
		Managing and sourcing resources, freelance, partners, internal resources on multiple initiatives.</li>
	<li>
		Market research - competitive analysis and module definition, based on published</li>
	<li>
		information, guest interviews, and client feedback</li>
	<li>
		Drive adoption through client training and marketing programs</li>
	<li>
		Prioritize and streamline tasks to ensure accuracy and efficiencies, proactively identifying issues / risks</li>
	<li>
		Maintain and continue to build strong client relationships to deliver world class service</li>
	<li>
		Define and provide performance metrics to internal and external clients</li>
	<li>
		Develop world class processes for all business activities, including hiring, client services,</li>
	<li>
		and product management</li>
	<li>
		Manage projects using Basecamp and other 37 signal tools</li>
</ul>
<p>
	QUALIFICATIONS:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Minimum 3 years experience in Producer / Project Management role</li>
	<li>
		Comfortable managing and driving multiple projects at a time</li>
	<li>
		Initiative to identify areas for improvement and define solutions</li>
	<li>
		Mobile and / or hospitality technology are highly desired</li>
	<li>
		Excellent oral, written, communication and follow up skills</li>
	<li>
		Strong attention to detail, organization and time / project management skills</li>
	<li>
		Likes to work in a team-oriented, collaborative atmosphere</li>
	<li>
		Ability to thrive in a fun, fast-paced, changing environment</li>
	<li>
		Happy, fun, and excited about the opportunity</li>
	<li>
		Ability to work from Santa Barbara office and or willing to move to Santa Barbara for thisjob.</li>
</ul>
